OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1777479067
OL,3,CIn full: King Charles' historic speech
OL,4,Cto Congress
OL,6,F"The story of the United Kingdom and
OL,7,Fthe United States is, at its heart, a
OL,8,Fstory of reconciliation, renewal and
OL,9,Fremarkable partnership.
OL,11,F"From the bitter divisions of 250
OL,12,Fyears ago, we forged a friendship that
OL,13,Fhas grown into one of the most
OL,14,Fconsequential alliances in human
OL,15,Fhistory.
OL,26,@nD@AOUsD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G40/43
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,317,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31641
SC,0041
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1777479067
OL,3,CIn full: King Charles' historic speech
OL,4,Cto Congress
OL,6,F"I pray with all my heart that our
OL,7,Falliance will continue to defend our
OL,8,Fshared values, with our partners in
OL,9,FEurope and the Commonwealth, and
OL,10,Facross the world, and that we ignore
OL,11,Fthe clarion calls to become ever more
OL,12,Finward-looking.
OL,14,F"Mr Speaker, Mr Vice-President,
OL,15,Fdistinguished ladies and gentlemen,
OL,16,FAmerica's words carry weight and
OL,17,Fmeaning, as they have since
OL,18,FIndependence.
OL,20,F"The actions of this great nation
OL,21,Fmatter even more.
OL,26,@nD@AOUvD@AOU|D@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G41/43
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,317,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31642
SC,0042
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1777479067
OL,3,CIn full: King Charles' historic speech
OL,4,Cto Congress
OL,6,F"President Lincoln understood this so
OL,7,Fwell, with his reflection in the
OL,8,Fmagisterial Gettysburg Address that
OL,9,Fthe world may little note what we say,
OL,10,Fbut will never forget what we do.
OL,12,F"And so, to the United States of
OL,13,FAmerica, on your 250th birthday, let
OL,14,Four two countries rededicate ourselves
OL,15,Fto each other in the selfless service
OL,16,Fof our peoples and of all the peoples
OL,17,Fof the world.
OL,19,F"God bless the United States and God
OL,20,Fbless the United Kingdom".
OL,26,@nD@AOUtD@AOU{D@AOU|D@YO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G42/43
